First time at this location. I’ve previously only been to Hyde Park location. I ordered using the website. Calzones were delicious and bigger than I remembered. Great service and nice portions for the price.
Fast and friendly!
Outstanding spot for cheap food. will surely make a return trip. food is like a restaurant in louisville i liked.

Probably the BEST calzone!! My favorite is the pepperoni calzone with the side ranch dressing. It is baked to perfection, it's melty cheese is delicious, the tomato sauce just right, and with a couple side dressings you can dip it or pour it on and have your taste buds explode with satisfying flavors. My friend mentioned it's Addictive food! Highly recommend!

Good as a fast food option, but a little too pricey. There are many more burger options in Chicago.  I've been to this location 3 times and the service/food has gotten better. There is usually a long line to order (you can do so either at the counter or on their new kiosks). To avoid the line, we ordered on the Pockets Restaurant.  Shack Burger: Can be ordered as a single or double, and the "Shack Sauce" is very good. This is my go-to order.  Shack Stack: A combination of a cheeseburger and their 'Shroom burger. The veggie portion is a breaded patty made with mushroom and cheese. Personally, the cheese was overwhelming.  Shake: We ordered the cookie and cream shake to share. It was good at first but gets to be too sweet.
I love Pockets! It is great, fresh, delicious food. I only know of Pockets in Chicago on Southport. They seemed to have closed all the other locations. Worth the drive!
Nice dudes, yummy food
Delicious!! I got the Asian quinoa bowl with chicken, it was fantastic. Tasty, healthy, and inexpensive. I’m gonna start eating here a LOT more often...
My husband’s burger was really good he said. My food was not warm enough. Enjoyed the onion strings.

I wanted to give a shoutout to the Great customer service I received on 06/06/20(Saturday). The gentleman who gave me my order was extremely Great. We had a small chat about me traveling all the way from Elgin IL just to pickup food for my family and I. We all love Pockets, we’re sad that the closest one to us closed up. We appreciate the Awesome food. The gentleman was extremely sweet and gave us a couple of fountain drinks on the house. That was extremely kind of him. Thank you Sooooo much for preparing and getting our food together. Everyone enjoyed their meal. 💗💗💗🥰🙌🏼
Great food! Food was very good. Only problem I had was the time to receive our food but it was worth the wait. The server was very nice.

Yesterday was the first time we visited this good restaurant. But It is obviously not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the attentive service, with the excellent  cuisine and booze and with the comfortable charge. We will absolutely go back there again.

Love their calzones. Thats my go to but the chicken chili soup is amazing too. Not to mention it is a giant bowl of soup. Easily can be shared with 2. And if your a salad lover this place is definitely for you. All kinds of greens that are fresh and even greater choices of toppings. Definitely a place i recommend if your close by.

I love Pockets. I've always loved Pockets since they opened their first restaurant on Clark (no longer there). I've been going for probably 25 years.  My husband likes the calzones, my daughter likes the kids pizza and I love my Original Turkey Pocket with house dressing... its ALWAYS made perfectly.   Everyone is happy!  Go and you'll be happy too.

Went in asked for an order under my fiance's name and was given someone else's order went back to return the food and manager was pissed because the girl at the register messed up and gave me and had me pay for someone else's order. Upon returning the food and asking for my money back the person who's order it belongs to went to pick it up and took the receipt. The daytime manager with the glasses was very unprofessional and mad because the little girl at the register gave me the wrong order.
The salads are very tasty. My favorite is the cobb salad. It has everything you could want from a cobb salad, and a bready pocket. I typically ask for a side of marinara to dip the pocket into.

I am an avid pockets fan because of the meaty calzone. That is all I get and I love it. Its huge and its hits the spot! This time around, me and my gf ordered 2 calzones since this was her first time. After waiting for more than 45 minutes(They said it would take 20), we get these tiny calzones! literally both calzones combined were smaller than the calzone I usually get when I pick up from their other locations(pictures below to compare).Also, ordered mine with grilled chicken and I saw the dude just microwave the chicken and opening the calzone with a knife to add it in. For ~$10 a calzone, they are not worth it for this size.Don't waste your money here.Get a pizza from papa johns or from the frozen isle instead.
great but too expensive

I'd give this review 4-stars if Pockets wouldn't keep raising the prices of their product.  In 2011, I used to buy pockets for $5.99 which included any kind of added meat and a punch card that added up to a free pocket after 10-purchases. In 2017, this same order costs $7.99 + 1.50 for any meat and there is no incentive / punch card to keep coming back. I can't Justify paying $9.49 for a roll and some lettuce.  Go to Jewel and create your own "pocket" at the salad bar and a wheat roll from the bakery- it's the same quality and will run you about $4-5 total.
Food was fine and service was quick (though our order wasn't correct). I would go back for a quick bite.

The food is truly healthy fast food!  The calzones are not as greasy. The staff is friendly and they keep expanding their menu selection. I used to totally be addicted when I lived in Lombard. I was totally sad when they closed. Moved to the city and this one was open with the same charm but they added pizza!  And frozen yogurt.  We love it!  Something for the vegetarian in me,  my meat eating husband and my picky son.  Why the four starts?  Ordering online can be a hassle as you may have the order in twice.

Great pockets that are really satisfying. I am always left satisfied when I eat my lunch here. The price is great and the place is nice as well. My favorite is the Southwest pocket. The ingredients itself is a great mix and really delicious.

Aside from the tasty pockets they have, I also love the calzones especially the BBQ chicken calzone. Gotta love the taste that sips in your mouth and leaves a lingering flavor. The BBC calzone (bacon,broccoli, cheddar) is also a must try. I always end up feeling satisfied after every meal I had here. Really worth it every penny. I would definitely recommend this place especially to new visitors.

Arrived to this place around lunch and ordered this Buffalo Pocket with Chicken. It was really good. The flavor really hits the mouth. In fact I can still remember the taste of it right now. The price was just about right and I couldn't be more satisfied than that. Would definitely come back here again to try the other "pockets" they have on the menu.

They are incredibly slow here.  The people are nice and depending how busy they are they've been known to have a ever expanding delivery area.  It's expensive for what it is but the calzones are good and the salads are large enough to share or have a second meal from.  A little less likely to order from here as the North Ave location is now gone.
